This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with automatic speech recognition (ASR) which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Transformer-based encoder-decoder architectures which are commonly used in NLP tasks. 

It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech recognition, which is a sound-based task. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for ASR and the compression of these networks. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category as ASR is a subfield of AI and the paper deals with improving the performance of ASR models. 

Finally, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of edge devices for ASR, which could be considered a control system.
